    public abstract static class Tracker.SemanticObjectItem<P extends Semantics.Primitive>
extends Tracker.Item<java.lang.Integer,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,P>
    The implementation of an Tracker.Item with Integer shape identifier and OWLNamedIndividual as ID.

    This is a special type of tracked Tracker.Item, which can deal with the semantic object hierarchy (with root class: Semantics.Primitive).
    In particular, it describes the shape of the Objects with integer values that can be easily checked by using: isUndefined(), isPrimitive(), isOrientable(), isSphere(), isPlane(), isCone() and isCylinder() (see: Tracker.Item.getShape(Object)).

    Also, it contains the definition (as constants) of the confusion matrix of the error in recognise objects shapes on a table top scenario published in:
    Buoncompagni, Luca, and Fulvio Mastrogiovanni. "A Software Architecture for Object Perception and Semantic Representation." Workshop on Artificial Intelligence and Robotics (AIRO 2015).
    Those results are obtaining by using the Primitive Identification Tagging and Tracking (PIT) ROS architecture.

    Last but not the least, it poses the basic interface to thw aMOR and OWl interface by forcing Tracker.Item parameters to be:

    • 'I' an OWLNamedIndividual, which defines an unique semantic object.
    • 'P' an extension of Semantics.Primitive.
    • 'S' an Intger.

    • Method Detail

      • getShape

        public java.lang.Integer getShape(P object)

        Assign tho this item its shape by looking on Semantics.Primitive class hierarchy. Te returning value is automatically assigned to Tracker.Item.shape during Tracker.Item constructors.

        More in particular, it returns:

        • PRIMITIVE_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Primitive,
        • SPHERE_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Sphere,
        • ORIENTABLE_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Orientable,
        • PLANE_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Plane,
        • CONE_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Cone,
        • CYLINDER_SHAPE_TAG if object instaceof Semantics.Cylinder,
        • UNDEFINED_SHAPE_TAG otherwise.
        Specified by:
        getShape in class Tracker.Item<java.lang.Integer,org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLNamedIndividual,P extends Semantics.Primitive>
        Parameters:
        object - the semantic object to track.
        Returns:
        an integer state identifying the objects shape.
        See Also:
        isUndefined(), isPlane(), isPrimitive(), isSphere(), isOrientable(), isPlane(), isCone(), isCylinder()
